      • isInRange

        public static boolean isInRange(java.lang.Object source,
                java.lang.Object begin,
                java.lang.Object end,
                boolean inclusive)
        Determines if a date is within a specified range.
        Parameters:
        source - Date to check.
        begin - Begin date range.
        end - End date range. (must be after begin)
        inclusive - Flag indicating to include begin and end as valid dates for checking.
        Returns:
        Flag indicating if source is (after begin) AND (before end); OR (if inclusive is true) equal to begin or equal to end.

      • getDaysBetween

        public static int getDaysBetween(java.lang.Object object0,
                 java.lang.Object object1)
        Gets the days between two Dates. Spawns Calendar objects from the arguments, and returns the number of days between them. Returns a negative value if the first argument is after the second argument.
        Parameters:
        object0 - First object from which a Calendar object can be constructed.
        object1 - Second object from which a Calendar object can be constructed.
        Returns:
        Days between the two objects. Maximum days is 2,147,483,647, a range of nearly 5.9 million years.

      • getBusinessDaysBetween

        public static int getBusinessDaysBetween(java.lang.Object object0,
                         java.lang.Object object1,
                         java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> holidays)
        Gets the days between two Dates, excluding Saturdays, Sundays, and (optionally) Holidays. Spawns Calendar objects from the arguments, and returns the number of days between them. Returns a negative value if the first argument is after the second argument.
        Parameters:
        object0 - First object from which a Calendar object can be constructed.
        object1 - Second object from which a Calendar object can be constructed.
        holidays - Holiday days (as Calendary.DAY_OF_YEAR) to exclude
        Returns:
        Business Days between the two objects. Maximum days is 2,147,483,647, a range of nearly 5.9 million years.

      • getHoursBetween

        public static long getHoursBetween(java.lang.Object object0,
                   java.lang.Object object1)
        Gets the hours between two Dates. Spawns Calendar objects from the arguments, and returns the number of days between them. Returns a negative value if the first argument is after the second argument.
        Parameters:

        public static Dates get(java.lang.String key)

        Parameters:
        key - Key value to check for equality against the the TimeFormatter or a match to the TimeFormatter.
        Returns:
        First found TimeFormatter. Null if no name or format equality or match found.

        public static java.util.Date getDate(java.lang.Object date,
                     java.lang.Object time)
                              throws java.lang.NullPointerException,
                                     java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Gets a Date object. Creates a New Date object from the passed in arguments.
        Parameters:
        date - Source from which to get the DATE portion of the new Date object. If null then the value from time will be used.
        time - Source from which to get the TIME portion of the new Date object. If null then the value from date will be used.
